Photo by The University of Oxford on August 11, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'beaaม Of a study of 200 million Facebook users, 28% (56.3 million) revealed sexuality- related information. According to Oxford's Dr Kashyap, younger generations are more likely to see their sexuality as 'an important aspect of their identity'.'.

Photo by The University of Oxford on August 11, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, sky and text that says 'The study found that women in their 20s and early 30s are twice as likely as older women to identify as bisexual. Women are also more likely to identify as bisexua or homosexual than men.'.

Photo by The University of Oxford on August 11, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Connor Gilroy of the University of Washington worked with Dr Kashyap on the study. 'There are large generational differences, as younger social media users share their sexualities much more than older users. For older users, marital status often substitutes for their sexual identity, whereas single people are more likely to disclose their sexuality.''.
